The paper discusses the development and implementation of a control strategy for a humanoid robot to react to external disturbances, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed strategy is based on the Capture Point concept, which involves predicting the future location of the robot's center of mass and generating references for the momentum-based torque controller, indicating a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions experiments in a simulator and on the iCub humanoid robot, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
